G.2 Regularity Assumptions.

1. $\mathcal{L}(\theta)$ is $L$-smooth and locally $\mu$-convex in neighborhoods of minima.
2. $\|\nabla \mathcal{L}(\theta)\| \leq G_{\max}$ almost everywhere (standard for overparameterized transformers with normalization layers).
3. $\mathbb{E}[\xi_t | \theta_t] = 0$, and $\text{Cov}(\xi_t | \theta_t) \approx \frac{\eta}{B} H(\theta_t)$ (aligned noise assumption).
4. $\|\mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_i} F \mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_j}\|_F \leq \epsilon_D \to 0$ as $D \to \infty$ (block-diagonal dominance).
5. $\delta > \lambda \|\mathcal{P}_{\mathcal{M}_G} \theta^*\|^2$ (signal-to-decay threshold).

